A business reborn!  I have not lived in Malden or Massachusetts all my life I'm a transport. Who fell in love with this little town.  When I first moved to Malden I frequented Jay's Ice Cream 🍦 and Pizza 🍕 the food was fresh as well as the Ice Cream.  Somewhere along the way things changed and NOT for the better.  The restaurant at 1 point made me wonder if they were ever inspected in this town.  Ice Cream was freezer burned the staff was unfriendly and you saw the decline fast and furiously.  Less cars 🚗 in the parking lot on a summer Sunday.  Their are quite a few bad reviews somewhere on the internet about them from me. I just stopped any relationship with that restaurant.  New Owner New Passion  Fast forward to the present...... the Staff is friendly and professional. The food fresh and delicious.  The restaurant clean and upgraded.  If you were a fan of Jay's back in the day.  If you stopped your patronage for the same reasons as I. Then you need to know Jay's has been reborn.  I have been there quite a bit lately. Still reasonably priced meals and of course fresh creamy delicious 🧊 🍦.  You scream they scream we all scream for ICE CREAM!

STAY AWAY!  I took my wife and three young kids (ages 2, 6 and 9) to try to get a Christmas tree at Jay's Pizza and Ice Cream yesterday.  We were verbally assaulted by the owner!  All we did was ask the price of the tree. He muttered some nasty words in the direction of my wife and stormed off.  When I asked what the issue was, he said my wife and I were rude to him and needed to apologize to him!  If we did, he'd be happy to sell us a tree. If not, he would "escort us off the premises!" We were in no way rude. We had just walked in to buy a tree there as we have for the last 10 years. We simply asked what the price was.  I went into the store to try to find out who the owner was, and what their affiliation was with the Christmas tree people. He followed me in, took out his cell phone and threatened to call the cops! (Which would have been fine if I was there alone... I didn't think my kids needed more trauma that night!)  My wife took our kids, all very upset of course, back to the car.... no tree.  The only information I could get was that his name is George. He refused to let me speak with anyone else there and came up towards me to physically remove me from the building! I left!  I called back today to see if the owner was available. Apparently George is the owner. He hung up on me.  I called the police to report him today, and they said they've gotten many complaints about him.  I'm not sure what his issues are, but he needs help. It's sad that our Christmas tree tradition had to end like that! I know kids have to learn about dealing with rude people, but shopping for a Christmas tree wasn't the time I thought we'd be dealing with that issue.  As a side note, although we've never really liked the food, we've gone to Jay's for ice cream before. We love supporting local businesses and we love our neighborhood. So this was particularly sad.  On a happier side note:  When we got back in the car last night, we googled "Christmas Tree Malden," and found VFW Christmas Trees and Wreaths on 114 Mystic Ave in Medford. We went right over, got a great tree, (they were super nice, btw), and proceeds support the VFW. As a bonus, they are located right near the real life "Grandfathers House" from the poem and song "Over the River and Through the Woods" which we sang as we drove by! New family tradition!

They refused to replace a quart of ice cream with their usual excellent brand after giving me an inferior brand without telling me!  I bought a quart of ice cream a couple of days ago that was not as good as usual.  I phoned and asked if it was still Richardson's (a wonderful ice cream).  The manager said that they had run out of that flavor and so what they given me was Hood ice cream.  I asked if they would replace it with a quart of Richardson's which is what I thought that I was buying and was told that they could not.  I find that appalling.  I ask for one product, am given another, and they will not replace it?  Ridiculous!   I don't plan to go there again.  Bye.
